{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 684062, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "Rozenberg", "body": "At the beginning of the fight, 8 (4 in 10-Man) adds are trapped in blocks of ice next to Hodir. You can break these blocks during the fight to free them and get their help. There are 4 kind of adds: Moonkins, Shamans, Mages, and Priests. Each type of add will use a special ability to help you against Hodir:\r\n\r\n[b]Moonkins[/b]: Starlight - Envelops a location in starlight for 1 min, increasing the attack and casting speed of friendly units within it.\r\n\r\n[b]Shamans[/b]: Storm Power - Charges a nearby friendly target with lightning, increasing critical strike damage by 135% for 30 sec.\r\n\r\n[b]Priests[/b]: Dispell - Priests will randomly dispell Freeze on the members of the raid.\r\n\r\n[b]Mages[/b]: Toasty fire - Warms nearby friendly creatures, preventing the effects of Freeze and Biting Cold, and increasing Spirit by 4. In addition, your Spells and Ranged attacks have a chance to singe enemies. Toasty fire can be extinguished by falling ice or Flash Freeze. \r\nSinged -  Singes the enemy, inflicting 3000 Fire damage and increasing damage taken from magical spells and effects by 2% for 25 sec. Stacks up to 30 times.", "date": "2009-04-19T02:35:24-05:00", "rating": 24, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "We all know that these Keepers of Ulduar are referrences of some of the most well-known Norsen Gods (Yes, there are incredibly many gods). Loken = Loki, Thorim = Thor, Mimiron = Mimir, Freya = Freja but what i don't know is what Hodir is a referrence to... anyone who knows or have a suggestion plz tell me as I am very curious :3", "creationdate": "2009-12-13T15:14:47-06:00", "id": 137030, "rating": 5, "commentid": 684062, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "menemew", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hodr][b]Hodr[/b],[/url], brother of Baldur,, decived by Loki to kill his own brother", "creationdate": "2010-01-04T19:35:11-06:00", "id": 141316, "rating": 8, "commentid": 684062, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "matoh", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Awesome thanks :D  Edit: correcting spelling -.-", "creationdate": "2010-01-27T00:41:11-06:00", "id": 145509, "rating": 2, "commentid": 684062, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "menemew", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Indeed, for many references within the game I think they are referring to Odin himself.", "creationdate": "2010-03-01T00:54:55-06:00", "id": 151798, "rating": 0, "commentid": 684062, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zephiros", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Actually i doubt that since Odin pierced on of his eyes to seem worthy to drink from the well of eternal wisdom. Hodir got both eyes so i think matoh is right", "creationdate": "2010-04-07T09:28:58-05:00", "id": 157892, "rating": 0, "commentid": 684062, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "448684", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 684096, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "353081", "body": "-Start the fight off by having the normal tank pull Hodir, and proceed to kill the Flash Freezes (~40k each) to free the four adds. The adds assist you an enormous amount in this fight, and keeping them alive is a huge benefit to your raid. Once all four adds are freed, start DPSing Hodir. Beware of Icicles hitting people (there will be an animation that looks like snow raining down as a warning for incoming icicles) they hit for a decent amount of damage. Much like the Keristrasza fight, you will recieve a damaging debuff if you stand still, you can remove stacks by moving, or simply jumping. The Moonkin NPC will periodically spawn beams of light (similar to the ones spawned by the Lunar Festival items), standing in them will give you a 100% haste buff, so get into those if possible.\r\n\r\nA raid warning will call out when Hodir begins casting Flash Freeze, at which point two large, light blue circles will appear on the ground. DO NOT stand in these circles, until icicles have fallen on them to leave a clearly visible mound of snow. As soon as the snow mound appears, EVERYBODY (tank included) must stand on these mounds, or they will be encased in flash freezes, and must be broken out immediately. The NPCs will also be frozen, and should be freed as soon as possible.\r\n\r\nThe other threat to this fight is Hodir's Frozen Blows ability. This weakens Hodir's physical damage considerably, however it adds a TON of frost damage to them. Have your frost resist tank taunt him IMMEDIATELY after gaining this buff. (On ten man with ~320 resist I was still getting hit extremely hard, so I recommend going to cap with your resist). The raid will take AoE damage which must be healed through during this phase (having raid members each wear a piece of frost resist is recommended to make it easier to heal through). When the buff is gone, the MT should taunt Hodir back immediately.\r\n\r\nThats as good of an explanation for the fight as I can give. All in all its not too bad of a fight. Good luck :)", "date": "2009-04-19T03:10:30-05:00", "rating": 52, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Pretty good explanation, one thing I like to change is have one tank with frost gear built into his defense set.  I have 417 frost resist with a paladin/shaman in my frost resist and still defense capped.  This allows extra dps slot to help bring him down faster.  For reference, I still had 20% dodge, 18% parry, and 20% block, and around 29k health unbuffed", "creationdate": "2009-04-26T12:26:28-05:00", "id": 94125, "rating": 14, "commentid": 684096, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "346382", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I use 2 piece of frost resist gear to tank this boss, the belt and the boots, together with pally aura.  I had 309FrR, 544def, 21% dodge, 17% parry, 21% block, 31k hp unbuffed.  I replaced my dodge trinket with a  http://www.wowhead.com/?item=39292   This will work also: http://www.wowhead.com/?item=36993  If you find your MT dying a lot or you want your OT to help dps.  Try getting a couple of pieces of the FrR gear and gem towards stam or defense cap.", "creationdate": "2009-05-04T23:36:27-05:00", "id": 96016, "rating": 6, "commentid": 684096, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "169025", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "My guild uses me as frost resistance tank, as a druid it's @#$% easy because tallented crit immune, so you can put on easy the three pieces of frost resistant gear. :-)", "creationdate": "2009-05-19T03:38:50-05:00", "id": 98814, "rating": 4, "commentid": 684096, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "32505", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "10 man is easy  i tank both phase with my frost resist gear on  505 frost resist with 542 def but not doable in 25man  hodir hits too hard", "creationdate": "2009-05-22T04:19:04-05:00", "id": 407177, "rating": 0, "commentid": 684096, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "310530", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
