{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 707750, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "90775", "body": "The Archivum Data Disc provides the following insights when the quest is turned in:\r\n\r\nHodir's sigil appears to be located inside a cache of artifacts.\r\nWatcher Hodir's temperament and behavior highly unstable.  Destruction of cache highly probably during prolonged combat.\r\nAllies present in the field of battle are likely to provide synergies and minimize combat duration.\r\nPreservation of cache is essential to recovering Hodir's sigil.", "date": "2009-05-06T16:29:33-05:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 708085, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "icantswim", "body": "I made the following 2 macros for my raid in order to mark the NPCs (marks show through the Flash Freezes), rather than the ice blocks themselves which is what you would get by trying to click on them all individually.\r\n\r\n/tar Field Medic Pen\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",1)\r\n/tar Field Medic Jes\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",8)\r\n/tar Missy\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",7)\r\n/tar Sissy\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",6)\r\n\r\n\r\n/tar Elementalist Mah\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",2)\r\n/tar Elementalist Avu\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",3)\r\n/tar Eivi\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",4)\r\n/tar Ellie\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",5)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThis allows the raid to track NPCs to help break them out of Flash Freezes and also prioritize which ones to break first (I personally prefer the mages first).\r\n\r\nSorry Horde, this macro is for the Alliance NPCs, but it could easily be tweaked to work for you guys to by changing the names.", "date": "2009-05-07T00:01:45-05:00", "rating": 44, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "/tar Battle-Priest Eliza /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",1) /tar Battle-Priest Gina /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",8) /tar Amira Blazeweaver /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",7) /tar Veesha Blazeweaver /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",6)  /tar Spiritwalker Tara /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",2) /tar Spiritwalker Yona /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",3) /tar Tor Greycloud /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",4) /tar Kar Greycloud /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",5)  For horde.", "creationdate": "2009-05-12T06:14:50-05:00", "id": 97471, "rating": 41, "commentid": 708085, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "rented", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[code]/tar Kar G /run s,t=SetRaidTarget,\"target\";s(t,1) /tar Battle-Priest E /run s(t,2) /tar Spiritwalker T /run s(t,3) /tar Amira B /run s(t,4) /tar Tor G /run s(t,5) /tar Spiritwalker Y /run s(t,6) /tar Battle-Priest G /run s(t,7) /tar Veesha B /run  s(t,8)[/code]   works too for horde if you want to use 1 macro instead of 2", "creationdate": "2009-06-05T16:59:47-05:00", "id": 102161, "rating": 16, "commentid": 708085, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Lucai", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "For 10-man alliance raiding, we only need one macro:  /tar Field Medic Pen /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",2) /tar Missy /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",5) /tar Elementalist Avu /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",3) /tar Ellie /script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",4)  This puts the \"moon\" symbol on the mage.", "creationdate": "2009-09-01T17:04:55-05:00", "id": 119755, "rating": 3, "commentid": 708085, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "wuphonsreach", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 709107, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "70338", "body": "On 10 man, we found that freeing Missy Flamecuffs first is the best way to go.  After each freeze, break her loose and she will free the rest of the NPCs, allowing the raid to focus DPS on Hodir rather than running around letting the other NPCs out.  Also, make use of the spotlights, they act similar to the spots in Kara, increasing your attack/cast speed by 100%.  If the tank can kite Hodir to the proper position, the raid  can stack in the light and burn him quickly.", "date": "2009-05-07T23:00:34-05:00", "rating": 24, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 713628, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "172622", "body": "For this fight, it is absolutely required to have \"Projected Textures\" checked in the video settings. When you're on the video settings screen, click effects and it's at the very bottom on the right. \r\n\r\nWithout this enabled, you will not be able to see where the snow is going to fall, resulting in an extremely large amount of raid damage that is going to severely stress the healers. However, this does not need to be enabled for the runes indicating an upcoming Snowdrift before Flash Freeze to be visible.", "date": "2009-05-12T04:09:01-05:00", "rating": 22, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 717341, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Olafski", "body": "[quote]There are two hard modes for this fight, both of which are timed. Defeating Hodir in under 3:00 minutes, and defeating him in under 6:00 minutes.[/quote]\n\nI (and the rest of my raid) must be stupid.. what is the reward for defeating him in under six minutes? I would assume at least an extra emblem or something. We defeated him in about 5 minutes twice now and we don't see any indication of seeing a \"hard mode\". \n\nDoes it perhaps apply to 25 man only?\n\nedit:\nThis is what I get from [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Hard_mode#Hodir]Wowwiki's Hard Mode list[/url]:\n[quote]Hodir has 3 different hard modes. Three minutes into the fight against Hodir, he destroys one frozen chest. Six minutes in, he destroys the second chest. Nine minutes into the fight he destroys the last chest and enrages. Therefore the two different hard modes are: Keeping all chests intact (Kill Hodir within 3 minutes) and Keeping 2 chests intact (Kill Hodir within 6 minutes). The regular mode is to kill Hodir in 6\u20139 minutes, only keeping one chest intact.[/quote]\n\nNothing about 25man, so I would think if you kill him within 3 minutes you get 3 chests, within 6 minutes you get 2 chests and between 6-9 minutes you only get one chest. So where is my hidden mystery chest? :(", "date": "2009-05-15T18:54:56-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "theres 1 hard mode and 1 hard mode only.  if you kill him sub 3 minutes you get extra loot.  if you are over 3 minutes and kill him its \"normal mode\"", "creationdate": "2009-05-15T19:26:37-05:00", "id": 98191, "rating": 18, "commentid": 717341, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "315419", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-05-15T18:58:42-05:00", 1, "Olafski"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 721609, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Khalaas", "body": "I do not think this is relevant to the topic, but I find Hodir's encounter extremely spectacular, with all these runes on the floor and constant snow and hail falling down.", "date": "2009-05-19T23:43:38-05:00", "rating": 21, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 722138, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sounder", "body": "Judging by the pin-map above, some groups are killing Hodir out in Auriaya's ring.  Anyone care to comment on this?  Is the idea to concentrate snowdrifts, cozy fires, and starlight into a more constrained area so they're easier to get to (and more likely to stack)?", "date": "2009-05-20T11:08:21-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "That is where Hodir stands after he is defeated.", "creationdate": "2009-05-20T11:48:23-05:00", "id": 99089, "rating": 6, "commentid": 722138, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "314609", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yes, the one standing in Auriaya's ring is a friendly version of Hodir. Since you actually [b]defeat[/b] and not kill him, he frees himself of Yogg-Saron's corruption and can be later asked to assist your raid during the showdown with Yogg.", "creationdate": "2009-05-20T12:39:46-05:00", "id": 99101, "rating": 8, "commentid": 722138, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Khalaas", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 723569, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "295749", "body": "I as Main Tank was able to withstand his Frozen Blows with only 250 Frost Resist. We successfully downed him in about 6mins. (Full T 7.5 + some Uld gear on). So it is possible without huge amounts of FR. Our healers were 1 Priest, 1 Pally, and 1 Druid.", "date": "2009-05-21T18:12:01-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I second that. The only one who really needs the frost resist gear is the MT and have some random pally in the raid use FR aura.", "creationdate": "2009-05-21T18:57:50-05:00", "id": 99359, "rating": 2, "commentid": 723569, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "369778", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-05-21T18:12:46-05:00", 1, "295749"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 725502, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Friction", "body": "Playing about in Wow model viewer, I've found that Hodir has a unique unarmed animation.\r\n\r\nIs he disarmable?", "date": "2009-05-23T20:29:56-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "No, he is not disarmable. Note that his unarmed attacks come in two types: one is left-hand punch and the second is a stomp. He holds his mace in the right hand. I did not have time to look closely during my guild's last fight with him, but I suspect he most likely combines these kicks and punches with weapon attacks.", "creationdate": "2009-05-24T01:01:03-05:00", "id": 99748, "rating": 5, "commentid": 725502, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Khalaas", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 732501, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kiliana", "body": "In order to do Hard Modes you will need approximately:\n[b]180,000 DPS (25)\n45,000 DPS  (10)[/b]\nThat is approximately, assuming 19 DPS and 7 DPS:\n[b]9,500 DPS\n6,500 DPS[/b]\nrespectively to meet the noted hard modes.\nThese figures negate the fact that you need to pop flash freezes and any DPS done by the NPCs.\nIf anyone can approximate the NPC DPS I'll update this again to accomodate for it.\n\n\n\n[i]Update: Removed 6min info and added comment pertaining to NPCs[/i]", "date": "2009-05-30T20:30:34-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "There is no 6 minute hard mode. The description of the fight is wrong.", "creationdate": "2009-06-04T08:20:05-05:00", "id": 101878, "rating": 3, "commentid": 732501, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "350969", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This of course doesn't take into account the tanks DPS, nor the NPCs DPS, both of which won't compare to the true DPSers, but it is certainly not negligible. My guess is somewhere in the range of 8000-8500 DPS for each of 19 DPS to successfully beat the hard mode timer (on heroic of course).  Recount is capable of tracking the NPCs DPS with a little tweaking of the settings.", "creationdate": "2009-06-07T18:10:09-05:00", "id": 102499, "rating": 5, "commentid": 732501, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Spiralphoenix", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-06-11T02:02:47-05:00", 1, "Kiliana"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 732711, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "224391", "body": "Tanking him on normal by feral druid I noticed one thing: when he turned on his frozen blows i popped BarkSkin and some of my Feral Defence procs made his melee strikes fully absorbed and the frost effect from the buff was not applied to me.\r\nIn other words, i suppose if you fully block/absorb his melee attack with Frozen Blows(that's real I think) you will not be damaged by frost, as if you parried/dodged/made him miss you.", "date": "2009-05-31T02:39:47-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Not sure if this is a bug, which it probably is, but for the time being this is true. Having a Power Word: Shield on you, or reducing the damage taken by his physical attack below your max block will mean that you will not be hit with the Frost portion of Frozen Blows. Because of this, a Frost Resist tank is highly unnecessary.", "creationdate": "2009-06-18T23:11:58-05:00", "id": 104607, "rating": 0, "commentid": 732711, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Niroshi", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 734406, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "gamerunknown", "body": "Just in case there's a really big Curse of Doom? \r\n\r\nAlso: [quote=\"Iconix\"][b]you don't actually kill him[/b] or any of the other \"keeper\" bosses for that matter (Mimiron, Thorim and Freya) you simply release them from Yogg-Saron's control\r\n\r\n[b]On another note, we killed Hodir[/b]... [/quote]\r\n\r\nHeh", "date": "2009-06-01T16:13:58-05:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 734621, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "204375", "body": "Okay, let me get this straight. I thrust your spear, polish your helm, and blow your horn, and [i]now[/i] I have to fight you, possibly killing me, and my friends, just so you can return back to normal? Did those dailys mean nothing to you? I thought we had something special!", "date": "2009-06-01T22:33:16-05:00", "rating": 147, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You thrusted his spear, polished his helm, and blew his horn.................... Bow chica bow wow", "creationdate": "2009-07-02T22:33:48-05:00", "id": 413746, "rating": 26, "commentid": 734621, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "167214", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Hey. His sons love ya. Unfortunately, they're stuck in Dun Niffelem and haven't found a way to get the message to dear old Dad. So he'll decide to love you as well... after you get Yogg-Saron out of his head first.", "creationdate": "2009-07-05T23:48:09-05:00", "id": 414194, "rating": 5, "commentid": 734621, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "330603", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Forget that... I save the advance guard's asses, breaking them out of ice and doing their job solo for them, and then when Hodir freezes me solid they can't even be bothered to thaw me out before leaving? Ridiculous.", "creationdate": "2014-12-16T15:50:11-06:00", "id": 814061, "rating": 0, "commentid": 734621, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Rizzwhit", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 744133, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "389224", "body": "I solo tank this as a frost resist capped prot pally.\r\nI have tried moving from beam to beam, so melee can get the buff, this can be problematic because the frost runes are very difficult to see underneath the light beams AND hodir.\r\n\r\nI have tried tanking him in a circular motion around the room, this works pretty good, but it can be risky as when he has frozen blows i can easily back into ranged/healers and theyll get hit extremely hard by the frozen blows aoe effect.\r\n\r\nLast night i kited him from  chest to chest, and we one shotted him.  I find that this was the best way to tank the fight, it was extremely easy to avoid frost runes, and when frozen blows was up, and i was about to turn him around to head back to the other side of the room, i just said it in vent so they wouldnt be right in front of me.  two healed it, pally/priest. only  had 2 ranged dps mage/boomkin, and then 3 rogues and a dk.\r\n\r\nVery easy fight, and very simple and fun to tank\r\n\r\n\r\nOh, one more thing, i let our holy pally do frost aura because he has aura mastery, and, while im fr capped, everyone else is not, so 240 fr for 10 seconds is excellent for frozen blows, as that is over 50% frost dmg reduction", "date": "2009-06-11T19:04:37-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 745879, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "372604", "body": "Sound files for this fight.\r\n\r\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Hodir\\\\UR_Hodir_Aggro01.wav\")\r\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Hodir\\\\UR_Hodir_Berserk01.wav\")\r\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Hodir\\\\UR_Hodir_Death01.wav\")\r\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Hodir\\\\UR_Hodir_FlashFreeze01.wav\")\r\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Hodir\\\\UR_Hodir_Slay01.wav\")\r\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Hodir\\\\UR_Hodir_Slay02.wav\")\r\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Hodir\\\\UR_Hodir_Stalactite01.wav\")\r\n/script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Hodir\\\\UR_Hodir_YSHelp01.wav\")", "date": "2009-06-13T17:07:07-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 750326, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "mykevelli", "body": "The description of his Biting Cold debuff states:\r\n[i]Biting Cold - Applies exponentially increasing damage-over-time Frost damage every 1 second to stationary targets. [u]Any form of movement will reset the number of stacks.[/u][/i]\r\n\r\nThe underlined part is not completely true.  Any form of movement will only remove a [b]single[/b] stack of the debuff.  This is an important distinction to make because otherwise you would be able to let the debuff stack to 3 or 4, strafe for a split-second and have the whole thing removed, which is not how it works.\r\n\r\nBecause movement only removes a single stack you have to be more mindful of the stacks you have on you and have to be sure to not fall behind on keeping the stacks off of you.", "date": "2009-06-18T12:27:09-05:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 753791, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dongolev", "body": "So, we've got Hodir and his sons...\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen do we fight Mrs. Hodir?", "date": "2009-06-21T13:55:49-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Mrs. Hodir is in reality, Sara.  Creepy isn't it?", "creationdate": "2009-06-22T05:51:39-05:00", "id": 412039, "rating": -1, "commentid": 753791, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Niroshi", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 758993, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "zapiks44", "body": "[quote]They also cast Conjure Toasty Fire, which prevents the effects of Biting Cold, [b]Flash Freeze[/b] and Freeze, [/quote]\r\n\r\nThis is untrue. Toasty Fire does NOT prevent Flash Freeze.", "date": "2009-06-26T09:25:59-05:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, verified last night that Toasty Fire does not prevent Flash Freeze.  Who does one ask to edit the top section of Wowhead articles?", "creationdate": "2009-08-24T21:15:27-05:00", "id": 118185, "rating": 1, "commentid": 758993, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "244865", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 769567, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "gaeilge", "body": "the key to this fight, quite simply, are freeing the mages first.  Icon them, make sure they are always freed first.  they help free the iceblocks with \"melt ice\" and \"toasty fires.\"  melee, watch the \"singed\" debuff (which ranged will cast on hodir from dpsing near a toasty fire) on Hodir, you will get more benefit from your abilities that do \"spell damage.\"  forget all you know about you regular rotation, throw in your spell damage as much as you can on that high stack of \"signed.\"  we had a DK just dropping DND, IT, PS, DC and he was doing over 10k ticks with DND.  Just imagine what your mages, moonkin, warlocks and elemental shamans can do to him. =)", "date": "2009-07-06T11:53:18-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-07-06T12:35:50-05:00", 2, "gaeilge"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 778367, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "422006", "body": "In case anyone didn't notice, Hodir is a reference to Hodr, a blind Norse god who was tricked by Loki into killing his brother Baldr.", "date": "2009-07-14T21:55:44-05:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 780201, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "AddictedPoi", "body": "Here are some summarized tips that I've compiled after getting some experience with this fight. Using this strategy we got the boss down in 3.35 minutes (only because someone released more NPCs than intended). So...\r\nDon\u2019t release all NPCs! Save your time! Tank on the right side! (or left side)\r\n\r\nRelease [b]Mage NPC[/b] to get [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62821]Toasty Fire[/url][/b] Stand near campfires and DPS the boss to cause [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=65280]Singed[/url][/b]. The most important buff of all times! [b]60% more damage[/b] taken by the boss!\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=32893]Missy Flamecuffs[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33327]Sissy Flamecuffs[/url] are the two mages that drop [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62821]Toasty Fire[/url][/b]\r\n\r\nRelease [b]Shaman NPC[/b] to get [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=65133]Storm Cloud[/url][/b] on players. Bring the buff to the MT first and then stand near [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62821]Toasty Fire[/url][/b] to share [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=65134]Storm Power[/url][/b] with friends. WATCH your threat! You can [b]crit for 40k-80k[/b] with this if the boss is fully debuffed with [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=65280]Singed[/url][/b]\r\n\r\n[b]Moonkin NPCs[/b] cast [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62807]Starlight[/url][/b]. Increases attack and casting speed by 50%. Useful for unfreezing NPCs after [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=61968]Flash Freeze[/url][/b]. Useless in hard mode because they can be disregarded, thus leaving them in iceblocks where they will be killed by the first [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=61968]Flash Freeze[/url][/b].\r\n\r\nRaid damage comes from:\r\n1. [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62038]Biting Cold[/url][/b] Frost damage over time. Stacks. Hug [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62821]Toasty Fire[/url][/b]!\r\n2. [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=63512]Frozen Blows[/url][/b] The main part of the damage goes to the tank but the raid will suffer as well. People will need a bit of healing. [b]No frost resistance gear![/b] Only for the tank!\r\n\r\nNPC marking [b]macro[/b]. Alliance side. Releases mages and shammies.\r\n\r\n/tar Missy\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",7)\r\n/tar Sissy\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",6)\r\n/tar Elementalist Avuun\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",5)\r\n/tar Elementalist Mahfuun\r\n/script SetRaidTarget(\"target\",4)\r\n\r\nEnable [b]\"Projected Textures\"[/b] in Video options to be able to see runes on the floor.", "date": "2009-07-16T17:30:04-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-07-16T17:32:22-05:00", 2, "AddictedPoi"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 796018, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "87230", "body": "Something I thought is worth mentioning for [b]Resto Druids[/b].\r\n\r\nFrozen Blows is triggered almost right after Flash Freeze, so during Flash Freeze hotting everyone with Rejuvenation helps tremendously. After I realized the simple fact about Frozen Blows timing, it was a lot easier healing through it, as I was able to time my HoTs correctly.", "date": "2009-08-02T15:14:12-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 34, "id": 811465, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Plasteremiten", "body": "During this encounter, it's not good to use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=21536]Elune Stones[/url]. I learned the hard way.", "date": "2009-08-14T12:16:23-05:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
