{"commentv2": 1, "number": 54, "id": 1837449, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Qairon", "body": "Soloed 25-man mode with enhancement shaman ilvl 488. He nearly enraged on me. Nothing special about the fight itself, just rotated my defensive cooldowns on [spell=63512]. Started the fight by blowing all my offensive cooldowns and then just using them as they came up. It's basicly just a dps race, don't unfortunately remember my average dps on the fight. Of course the most important thing is not to get frozen on the fight, so get on that patch of ice when it comes up. He also occasionally roots you, but fortunately the icicles that drop don't hit that much. Keep moving all the time, there is a stacking debuff if you don't, use [spell=58875] if you have to.\n\nI used [spell=117013] and [spell=16166] as my offensive talent choices, [spell=108281] and [spell=108270] as my defensive. I also had glyphed wolves, [item=43344] and [item=41531]. He hits quite hard so I used my maelstrom stacks mainly on heals, and when my wolves or AG was up, on lightning bolt.", "date": "2013-04-01T04:52:06-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-04-01T04:56:27-05:00", 1, "Qairon"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 1845511, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Wazdakka", "body": "So I was soloing this guy on 10 normal, ilvl 477 90 affliction warlock, and my only wipe came because my voidwalker died and he came after me. Even after soulburning another, he wouldn't be taunted and I was swiftly crushed.\r\n\r\nOn my second try, the voidwalker died again, but I was able to use Dark Bargain, Harvest Life, and Healthstone to survive long enough for my voidwalker to regain aggro. I got rooted a lot, which was bothersome. I used EMFH on cooldown. \r\n\r\nSelf buffed, using 250 intellect food. \r\n\r\nThe fight would have been a lot easier if I had maybe a Scroll of Fortitude, 275-300 intellect food, and some gems in my gear.", "date": "2013-04-21T10:48:09-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 56, "id": 1872429, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Morbius", "body": "Soloed the 10 player version with my 85 blood DK in 417 ilevel gear including Jade Forest greens and auction house blues.\n\nThe fight is easy it's just long. The only things you have to worry about are [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=61968]Flash Freeze[/url] and falling ice. To avoid [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=61968]Flash Freeze[/url] you have to stand on a snowdrift formed by falling ice. A large targeting circle will appear in the spot where the snowdrift will form. Also if you stand still too long you will build up stacks of [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=62038]Biting Cold[/url] that do progressively more damage. So keep moving.\n\nBe careful because falling ice can knock you back so try to keep it from landing on you. Any falling ice not just the one that forms the snowdrift. You can be hit by [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=62469]Freeze[/url], a spell that roots you in place, which will make it hard to avoid falling ice but apparently you won't be knocked back if you're frozen.\n\nIf you can avoid [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=61968]Flash Freeze[/url] for the whole fight you get an achievement called [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=2961]Cheese the Freeze[/url]. Which I did for this fight. There are 4 other [url=http://www.wowhead.com/search?q=hodir#achievements]achievements[/url] one of which is [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=2967]Getting Cold in Here[/url]. There are 4 NPCs that are frozen in ice. If you can break them out and keep them alive they will buff you. If you can keep them alive the whole fight you will get an achievement called [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=2963]I Have The Coolest Friends[/url].\n\nHere's the video:\nhttp://youtu.be/BexAw01qMuE", "date": "2013-06-30T21:16:29-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-07-04T22:23:03-05:00", 2, "Morbius"]}
