{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 711073, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "237317", "body": "Is he a [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Titan]Titan[/url]?", "date": "2009-05-09T19:54:10-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "No, he may be quite mighty but Hodir is not a titan.  He is, however, one of the closest beings to the titans as he was left on Azeroth by them to watch over the relics that were left behind.  Like the other ancient races he is made of a substance from the earth, metal to be precise, much like how the dwarves were all originally made from stone and metal. (See [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?zone=1337]Uldaman[/url] for some classic examples of these [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=7309]dwarves[/url]; there are also the newer, friendlier [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=29980]versions[/url] seen ", "creationdate": "2009-05-09T19:54:11-05:00", "id": 405518, "rating": 4, "commentid": 711073, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sorcereo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Also we already got to fight and interact with few Titans.. The Maiden of Virtue (Karazhan), Thorim, Freya, Auriaya, Kologarn, Jotun, Lore Keeper of Norgannon, Archaedas, Ironaya, Loken, Strand of the Ancients Battlemaster, and there may be more that i won't bother searching.", "creationdate": "2009-06-07T05:05:01-05:00", "id": 409754, "rating": -1, "commentid": 711073, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "domacleod", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 732728, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "starsword", "body": "These are the versions of the Keepers who help you fight [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33288]Yogg-Saron[/url]:\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33410]Freya[/url]\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33411]Hodir[/url]\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33412]Mimiron[/url]\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33413]Thorim[/url]", "date": "2009-05-31T02:57:21-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 735037, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "369917", "body": "[quote]EDIT: Just some food for thought; Titans have power beyond mortal comprehension. There is no way they would be included in a raid, at least not at the present. This is also why you never see any direct confrontation with Sargeras, though he is very evil and many wish to kill him, they cannot. I wouldn't count out the possibility of Blizzard allowing us to have some direct contact with these god-like creatures eventually though[/quote]\r\n\r\nWell.. im not sure a being like Sargeras will not be added in a raid at some point.\r\nAlready in vanilla wow C'thun - one of the old gods - were added.\r\nAlso that we in wotlk already are fighting another old god - Yogg Saron - and the hardest boss encounter in wotlk will be The lich king\r\n\r\nAccording to rumors about new expansions then if the Maelstrom expansion is going to be released then we will face the whole naga empirer of Nazjatar with a mutated Queen Azshara to take care of.\r\nIn the Maelstrom expansion Blizzard also consider adding the tomb of Sargeras for a possible \"awakening\" event of him to defeat the fallen titan.\r\nAnd as a new expansion is more than a year away.. might even 2.. then i cant see what should come between us and a Sargeras encounter as players gets stronger all the time.", "date": "2009-06-02T10:34:10-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 757792, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "stathisdjs", "body": "Hodir is also joked as Hoo Dear...", "date": "2009-06-25T04:23:30-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 684054, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "353081", "body": "-Start the fight off by having the normal tank pull Hodir, and proceed to kill the Flash Freezes (~40k each) to free the four adds. The adds assist you an enormous amount in this fight, and keeping them alive is a huge benefit to your raid. Once all four adds are freed, start DPSing Hodir. Beware of Icicles hitting people (there will be an animation that looks like snow raining down as a warning for incoming icicles) they hit for a decent amount of damage. Much like the Keristrasza fight, you will recieve a damaging debuff if you stand still, you can remove stacks by moving, or simply jumping. The Moonkin NPC will periodically spawn beams of light (similar to the ones spawned by the Lunar Festival items), standing in them will give you a 100% haste buff, so get into those if possible.\r\n\r\nA raid warning will call out when Hodir begins casting Flash Freeze, at which point two large, light blue circles will appear on the ground. DO NOT stand in these circles, until icicles have fallen on them to leave a clearly visible mound of snow. As soon as the snow mound appears, EVERYBODY (tank included) must stand on these mounds, or they will be encased in flash freezes, and must be broken out immediately. The NPCs will also be frozen, and should be freed as soon as possible.\r\n\r\nThe other threat to this fight is Hodir's Frozen Blows ability. This weakens Hodir's physical damage considerably, however it adds a TON of frost damage to them. Have your frost resist tank taunt him IMMEDIATELY after gaining this buff. (On ten man with ~320 resist I was still getting hit extremely hard, so I recommend going to cap with your resist). The raid will take AoE damage which must be healed through during this phase (having raid members each wear a piece of frost resist is recommended to make it easier to heal through). When the buff is gone, the MT should taunt Hodir back immediately.\r\n\r\nThats as good of an explanation for the fight as I can give. All in all its not too bad of a fight. Good luck :)", "date": "2009-04-19T02:23:35-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Using one tank is also a viable strategy.  A DK with one or two pieces of FR would do well, though we used a single warrior tank last night on normal.  I can't speak for heroic mode; It may very well require a frost resist tank, but normal is fine with one tank.  Make sure you're video settings are set properly to see the runes on the ground.  At the lowest settings I believe you can see the Flash Freeze runes, but he also puts smaller runes down under the frozen rain that make it MUCH easier to see exactly where the icicles will land.  Standing near the mage is very useful.  He drops bon fire", "creationdate": "2009-04-19T02:23:36-05:00", "id": 400771, "rating": 4, "commentid": 684054, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Absentiment", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Not sure why the above comment got rated down. We did this on regular (10man) difficulty with no frost resist. I'm not sure if we even had a paladin aura up.  Our first attempt half the raid didn't even see the icicles or the the snow piles. In video settings make sure your \"Projected Textures\" is checked, and turn your \"Particle Density\" slider all the way down. That way you can see all of the incoming icicles as runes on the ground and be able to dodge them easily. Healers spent most of their time in the moonlights, so chain heal, prayer of mending, and such were working wonders during the F", "creationdate": "2009-04-19T02:23:36-05:00", "id": 401257, "rating": 2, "commentid": 684054, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "130995", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-19T02:30:27-05:00", 3, "353081"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 689548, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "176340", "body": "So this is the guy who we've been raising spears and polishing helms for.", "date": "2009-04-22T16:05:17-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 704048, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vlad", "body": "[b]This Hodir is [u]not the one you fight[/u], the one you fight is here: http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=32845[/b]\r\n\r\nThis Hodir on the other hand will spawn after you defeat him. You may talk to him and trigger the only option available in his gossip: [i]\"Lend us your aid, keeper. Together we shall defeat Yogg-Saron.\"[/i] When you click this option he just disappears and yells [i]\"The veil of winter will protect you, champions!\"[/i]. He will now assist you with his powers when you fight Yogg-Saron later on. He will then spawn as [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33411]this NPC, also named Hodir[/url].\r\n\r\nHe also says (for those interested):\r\n[quote]Mortals, I am indebted to you for freeing me from the terrible corruption that besets this place. Though I have not yet recovered fully, I can help you battle [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33288]Yogg-Saron[/url].\r\n\r\nI can grant you and your friends the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=62650]Fortitude of Frost[/url], increasing your damage and reducing damage taken from enemy attacks. Should one of you be about to fall in battle, I can [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=64174]freeze you in a block of ice[/url], protecting you from all damage for a short time. Know that this ability taxes my power, and I must rest after using it.[/quote]", "date": "2009-05-03T15:05:58-05:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
